    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a grocery list deduplication assistant. Below is a grocery list grouped by section, in JSON format. Merge items that are clearly the same ingredient despite slightly different names or unit formats.\n\nRules:\n- Merge near-duplicates: \"shredded cheese\" + \"shredded cheddar cheese\" → keep the more specific name, sum quantities\n- Standardize units to: tsp, tbsp, cup, oz, lb, clove, can, whole (no plurals)\n- Convert equivalent units before summing (e.g. 1 teaspoon + 2 tsp = 3 tsp)\n- Do NOT merge genuinely different items (e.g. \"olive oil\" vs \"sesame oil\")\n- Keep every item — do not drop anything that has no duplicate\n- Section must be one of: produce | protein | dairy | pantry | frozen | spice\n\nInput grocery list:\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.grocery_list, null, 2) }}\n\nReturn strict JSON only — no markdown fences, no prose.",
        "hasOutputParser": true
      },
